{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/andycoupe/web-dev/orchestrator/.orchestrator-worktrees/T-01KPVF6G5Q9MCGQJMXBAC626J9/web/src/screens/review/MergeDialog.tsx","old_string":"/**\n * MergeDialog — confirmation modal for the merge workflow.\n *\n * Opened when the user clicks \"Merge into <branch>\" on the ApprovedFooter.\n *\n * Phase machine:\n *   confirming → POST merge endpoint\n *     ↳ merging      → show spinner while in-flight\n *     ↳ drifted      → show drift warning + \"Merge anyway\"\n *     ↳ gate_failed  → show gate failure list + \"Back to review\"\n *     ↳ conflicted   → show conflict paths + open editor + retry\n *\n * When the merge succeeds, onSuccess() is called — the task will transition\n * to 'merged' via SSE and the footer will update in Review.tsx.\n */","new_string":"/**\n * MergeDialog — a confirmation popup that appears before merging changes.\n *\n * This is what users see when they click \"Merge\" on a code review. It asks them\n * to confirm they want to merge their changes, shows them what merge strategy\n * will be used, and handles any issues that come up (like merge conflicts or\n * failing checks). If something goes wrong, it shows the user what the problem is.\n *\n * Technical details:\n * Opened when the user clicks \"Merge into <branch>\" on the ApprovedFooter.\n *\n * Phase machine:\n *   confirming → POST merge endpoint\n *     ↳ merging      → show spinner while in-flight\n *     ↳ drifted      → show drift warning + \"Merge anyway\"\n *     ↳ gate_failed  → show gate failure list + \"Back to review\"\n *     ↳ conflicted   → show conflict paths + open editor + retry\n *\n * When the merge succeeds, onSuccess() is called — the task will transition\n * to 'merged' via SSE and the footer will update in Review.tsx.\n */"}